." Manpage for ai
.TH ai 1 "February 2026" "setmy.info" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ai \- print AI profiles with environment variable substitution
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ai
.I [PROFILE]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B ai
command prints Markdown content from AI profile files located in the system-wide
directory or the user's home directory.
.PP
Arguments are profile names. For each
.I PROFILE
provided, the command looks for a file named
.I <PROFILE>.md
in the following locations (in order):
.IP 1. 2
User home directory:
.I $(smi-home-location)/ai/<PROFILE>.md
.IP 2. 2
System-wide directory:
.I $(ai-profiles-location)/<PROFILE>.md
.PP
If a profile file is found in either location, its content is processed through
.BR envsubst (1)
to substitute environment variables and then printed to standard output.
.PP
Additionally, for each profile processed, the command checks for a file named
.I ai.sh
in the current working directory. If it exists, it is sourced before processing the
profile, allowing for local environment variable definitions or script-based
customizations.
.SH EXAMPLES
Print contents of a single profile:
.PP
.nf
ai java
.fi
.PP
Print multiple profiles:
.PP
.nf
ai java maven springboot
.fi
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $(ai-profiles-location)/*.md
System-wide AI profile files (Markdown).
.TP
.I ~/.setmy.info/ai/*.md
User-specific AI profile files (Markdown).
.TP
.I ./ai.sh
Local script sourced for environment variable definitions.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR envsubst (1),
.BR smi-home-location (1),
.BR ai-profiles-location (1)
